            <title>[QPID-3716] Sun TCK tests expect an IllegalStateException thrown on invoking of Session#getTransacted() on closed session/connection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-3716</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sun TCK checks that Session#getTransacted() throws an IllegalStateException when invoked on closed session.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is an undocumented feature. I could not find a description of such behavior in both JMS Spec and JMS javadocs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This feature was present previously but was removed as part of failover functionality improvements.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
